SYNOPSIS
        string comma_number(int iValue)

DESCRIPTION
        Converts an integer to a string with commas separating each group
        of three digits. Negative values retain their leading minus sign.

EXAMPLES
        comma_number(0)          returns "0"
        comma_number(999)        returns "999"
        comma_number(1000)       returns "1,000"
        comma_number(123456789)  returns "123,456,789"
        comma_number(-1234567)   returns "-1,234,567"

SEE ALSO
        format_time(E), sprintf(E)
